               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210606-58-person769">
                  CHARLES 
                  CHRISTMAS
               <interp inst="t18210606-58-person769" type="surname" value="CHRISTMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210606-58-person769" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210606-58-person769" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an inspector of Bank notes, this note, No. 84,276 is forged in all respects, it purports to be signed Gordin, there was such a signing clerk, it is not his hand writing, (looks at No. 73,421) this is also forged in every respect, and off the same plate, and signed A. Consett, it is not his hand writing - they have been creased, but not used much.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210606-58-person770">
                  GEORGE 
                  GORDIN
               <interp inst="t18210606-58-person770" type="surname" value="GORDIN"></interp>
